A lab-grown 4ct D-VVS1 at $9,680 vs a natural 4ct G-VS2 at $71,290: this is $61,610 — the price of a house deposit in many countries. The lab-grown stone is D colorless (not G near-colorless), VVS1 clarity (not VS2), and 4ct (identical face-up size). The only difference is origin.

At 4ct, the lab-grown argument is the most compelling it gets at any size. The natural scarcity premium is highest here; the lab-grown price compression is deepest.

